<tr>
	<td class="alt1">
	<!-- message, attachments, sig -->
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<span class="time"><strong>Explain what is the role of a Monk in groups today.</strong></span>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#606B73" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Having read many of the monk forums it seems that a monk's usefulness to a<br />
group has been diminished.  Rogues are sought after more due to the fact<br />
that they can out damage a monk.  Warriors are sought after due to their<br />
mitigation advantage and their new abilities to generate hate.<br />
<br />
After many parses of higher level monks it appears that there is a soft cap<br />
on monk ac of 1340.  After that point, additional AC has little to no return<br />
value.  Monks go through life with weight restrictions but, higher level<br />
monks who actually are able to get their hands on excellent gear can easily<br />
blow the 1340 AC soft cap away.  Then weight seems to no longer be an issue.<br />
Big deal if you are over weight as a Monk, as long as your AC is over 1340<br />
then you are still maxed out on your defense potential.<br />
<br />
The Monk Mitigation Nerf took place before POP was released.  Having<br />
researched this subject I learned that the nerf was intended to slow down<br />
the top 5% of Monks but ended up hurting the entire class.  Now, some 18+<br />
months after the Monk Mitigation Nerf, monks still have problems with POP<br />
and above mobs going through them like a meat grinder.  Low end monks that<br />
do not have decent equipment have this problem magnified.<br />
<br />
One of the motivations for the Nerf seems to have been that Warriors were<br />
complaining that they were being overlooked by groups for tankage duty or at<br />
the least had to compete with Monks for tankage duty.  Well warriors now<br />
have their new hate producing toys that Monks do not.  Since this is the<br />
case, why not give Monks back their original mitigation abilities?<br />
Beastlords who are suppose to be hybrids of monks can already out damage<br />
monks and bring valuable tools to groups.  Rogues can out damage monks,<br />
Warriors and Knights can generate more hate than monks and also have much<br />
more hit points and better damage mitigation than monks.  Other than pulling<br />
old world yard trash what else can monks do that would make high end groups<br />
want them?<br />
<br />
LM<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
