		<!-- message -->
		<div><font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; Where exactly are monks being put through the meat grinder?  Monks aren't<br />
&gt; warriors, paladins, or shadow knights.  I as a necromancer have &quot;tanked&quot;<br />
&gt; named in BoT.  Monks with which I am guilded have off tanked Sol Ro trash<br />
&gt; mobs.  So unless you are talking elemental/Sol Ro minis/named, where is it<br />
&gt; that monks are incapable of surviving an encounter with a PoP mob?  If you<br />
&gt; mean monks are not making effective tanks for xp groups, then I would</font><br />
agree<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; with you, but I would also add that it isn't their role.</font><br />
<br />
Every other pure melee mitigates damage better than a Monk.  Druids, Clerics<br />
and Rangers even mitigate better than a Monk.  Monks are currently the<br />
definition of what  Paper Tank is.  The class should be able to take hits<br />
when landed on them better than they can now.  Monks do not have the HPs<br />
that Warriors and Knights have so giving Monks back their mitigation at the<br />
pre-nerf level would not mean the known tanking classes would have anything<br />
to fear about being pushed into obsolete area of groups.  Also get rid of<br />
the Hard Cap on AC that Monks have right now.  1340 is the magical AC number<br />
that senior monks have concluded is the amount of AC that offered<br />
diminishing returns if you go over.  For example a monk who had 500 AC above<br />
1340 only saw hits doing 7 points less to himself than at 1340 AC.  With<br />
this hard cap like I posted earlier, once 1340 is reached monks no longer<br />
need to worry about their weight.  They can get as &quot;fat&quot; as they want as<br />
long as they have enough AC on their items to stay at 1340.  Other classes<br />
continue to benefit from AC.<br />
<br />
Tanking is not the issue as far as being Main Tanks.  But they should take<br />
blows as well as the other pure Melees and even finger wigglers out there.<br />
Monks have no tools at their disposal to generate hate other than beating on<br />
a mob.  Since they cannot keep agro then they cannot be Main Tanks of any<br />
POP exp group.  And that should not be their role.  But, they should be what<br />
the original developers (Prior to the new group of developers post Luclin)<br />
had a vision of, a class that carried a ton of offense and able to avoid<br />
being hit.<br />
<br />
LM<br />
<br />
<br />
</div>
