		<div><br />
&quot;Palindrome&quot; &lt;damon-nomad@tiscali.co.uk&gt; wrote in message<br />
news:rq7b80tirulgfjbbc7handjlcbvfnjkurt@4ax.com...<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; Hi Tolkeinfan<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; I agree with you.  I started a monk, and enjoyed it to start with,<br />
&gt; BUT...<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; Speaking from the low end of the class levels, (my monk is stuck at<br />
&gt; 20) I find it impossible to group these days.  Groups on my server<br />
&gt; almost never answer a &quot;Monk LFG&quot; hail, but take my hand off for my<br />
&gt; Rogue to join them.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; Monk weapons (I'm talking non-twink here) are sheer rubbish.  Get a<br />
&gt; pair of Polished Steel Ulaks (total price 6 plat when I bought them)<br />
&gt; and that's really about it until you can amass 30 or 40k.  As a Rogue,<br />
&gt; I bought a cheap piercing weapon that had a proc at level 1 - I DREAM<br />
&gt; of decent monk weapons...<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; [Bizarre Monk Weapon Interlude - - I laughably scraped the cash for an<br />
&gt; Adamantine Bo Stick, with an AE Lightning Proc, hoping to have<br />
&gt; something for my monk to look forward to when she levelled up a bit. I<br />
&gt; got my higher-level Beastlord to try it out and... the Lightning AE<br />
&gt; hit my Beastlord for over 100 damage  :D  I mean - a weapon that can<br />
&gt; inflict a potential 225 damage on the WIELDER :D  Sure, the mobs in<br />
&gt; the area took damage, but I'd rather my monk didn't risk electrocution<br />
&gt; every melee!!!  Gonna look like a scene out of a Jackie Chan movie -<br />
&gt; comic monk exits stage right - clothing scorched and tattered and hair<br />
&gt; smoking]<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; As for pulling, forget it - it isn't worth the mana to heal my monk,<br />
&gt; to be honest.  My mighty range weapons may irritate the mob into a<br />
&gt; charge, but arrows and spells are better.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; My &quot;mighty&quot; hand-to-hand skills can do some damage, but nukes and<br />
&gt; rogues are better.  (My rogue was regularly backstabbing for around a<br />
&gt; 100 at lvl 20, and had weapons that had damage procs as well).  A<br />
&gt; Warrior with reasonable armour and a Centi Shortsword (200plat or less<br />
&gt; on my server) can take and dish out damage that renders me<br />
&gt; superfluous, AND they can Taunt, too.<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
I know your pain.  There is no reason why monks should suffer mitigation<br />
penalties versus the other pure melees.  We do not want any special<br />
treatment, we just want to be on a level playing field and not buried in<br />
some poorly implemented nerf that was initiated because the tippy tops of<br />
the class were a wee bit too good.  Someone said monks are the leather<br />
wearers so it is justified.  If that is the case then bump up a monk's<br />
ability to avoid being hit.  Have an avoidance ability that is independent<br />
of AC and is affected by weight.  The more a monk is underweight the more he<br />
will dodge attacks.  I have also heard the idea about maybe monks will get<br />
the ability to be immune to mobs rampages.  Or immune to mobs riposting<br />
them.  Both of these would add value to the class without marginalizing the<br />
other melees.  As stated earlier, monks cannot generate agro to be main<br />
tanks but they should be able to off tank for awhile incase the main tank<br />
goes down.<br />
<br />
I guess my big question is can someone explain AC in EverQuest terms?  If a<br />
Warrior or Knight has 1800AC then why does it not help a monk to have 1800<br />
AC?   Is AC some mysterious concept floating above San Diego that developers<br />
look up to ever so often like looking into a crystal ball and trying to<br />
guess what it means?<br />
<br />
For those monks reading this that have not visited the official Everquest<br />
forums at eqlive.com I encourage you to go there.  The monk class forum is<br />
one of the most posted to forum of any class there and has very well written<br />
posts about the problems with the class as it stands now.<br />
<br />
LM<br />
<br />
