	<td class="alt1">
	<!-- message, attachments, sig -->
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<span class="time"><strong>Re: Explain what is the role of a Monk in groups today.</strong></span>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#606B73" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><br />
&quot;Palindrome&quot; &lt;damon-nomad@tiscali.co.uk&gt; wrote in message<br />
news:rq7b80tirulgfjbbc7handjlcbvfnjkurt@4ax.com...<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; Hi Tolkeinfan<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; I agree with you.  I started a monk, and enjoyed it to start with,<br />
&gt; BUT...<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; Speaking from the low end of the class levels, (my monk is stuck at<br />
&gt; 20) I find it impossible to group these days.  Groups on my server<br />
&gt; almost never answer a &quot;Monk LFG&quot; hail, but take my hand off for my<br />
&gt; Rogue to join them.<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
Never had a problem getting groups with the monk, at any level. What server?<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; Monk weapons (I'm talking non-twink here) are sheer rubbish.  Get a<br />
&gt; pair of Polished Steel Ulaks (total price 6 plat when I bought them)<br />
&gt; and that's really about it until you can amass 30 or 40k.  As a Rogue,<br />
&gt; I bought a cheap piercing weapon that had a proc at level 1 - I DREAM<br />
&gt; of decent monk weapons...<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
PSU's are &quot;about it&quot; until you spend 30-40k? How about knuckle dusters?<br />
Fighting batons? Bear hide gloves? Cane of the tranquil? Mudman enforcer?<br />
You *do* know how to use the bazaar search facility, don't you? 30-40k is<br />
more than enough to set you up with all your equipment needs up to the point<br />
where upgrades are no drop high end stuff.<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; [Bizarre Monk Weapon Interlude - - I laughably scraped the cash for an<br />
&gt; Adamantine Bo Stick, with an AE Lightning Proc, hoping to have<br />
&gt; something for my monk to look forward to when she levelled up a bit. I<br />
&gt; got my higher-level Beastlord to try it out and... the Lightning AE<br />
&gt; hit my Beastlord for over 100 damage  :D  I mean - a weapon that can<br />
&gt; inflict a potential 225 damage on the WIELDER :D  Sure, the mobs in<br />
&gt; the area took damage, but I'd rather my monk didn't risk electrocution<br />
&gt; every melee!!!  Gonna look like a scene out of a Jackie Chan movie -<br />
&gt; comic monk exits stage right - clothing scorched and tattered and hair<br />
&gt; smoking]<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
The ABS is known as the giant killer for a reason. Get to the max melee<br />
distance, and you won't get hit. As a beastlord it's even easier, once it<br />
procs, back up - the pet will keep the mob in one place. Get your MR up high<br />
enough, and it won't be a problem.<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; As for pulling, forget it - it isn't worth the mana to heal my monk,<br />
&gt; to be honest.  My mighty range weapons may irritate the mob into a<br />
&gt; charge, but arrows and spells are better.</font><br />
<br />
Monks have never been known for range damage. Once you have the mob's<br />
attention, it's done it's work.<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; My &quot;mighty&quot; hand-to-hand skills can do some damage, but nukes and<br />
&gt; rogues are better.  (My rogue was regularly backstabbing for around a<br />
&gt; 100 at lvl 20, and had weapons that had damage procs as well).  A<br />
&gt; Warrior with reasonable armour and a Centi Shortsword (200plat or less<br />
&gt; on my server) can take and dish out damage that renders me<br />
&gt; superfluous, AND they can Taunt, too.</font><br />
<br />
Might as well complain that the monk doesn't get ports and dots, while<br />
you're at it.<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; Rogues are better scouts, and THE best corpse-draggers in the<br />
&gt; business, too.  Feign Death??  Give me the Sneak/Hide combo any day of<br />
&gt; the week to walk past lethal mobs, and give me Evade in combats, and<br />
&gt; you can keep the Feign death  :D  Mend skill?  Don't make me laugh....<br />
&gt; I'd rather have a 30 point Heal Spell I could count on!<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
FD flopping is almost as good as hide &amp; sneak. Never had a problem on corpse<br />
retrievals for anyone. Monks have evade too. Just set up a macro to attack<br />
off, FD, Stand, attack on. Mend works every time once the skill goes over<br />
100, which is by the time you are level 19.. It's saved my life many, many<br />
times, and has made the difference between having to FD and finishing the<br />
fight. As for a 30hp heal, what do you think bandages are for? At 20, you<br />
will be healing up to 26hp a bandage (assuming you've worked on bind wound).<br />
That plus the mend takes you to 75% health, or higher if you bind up to 50%<br />
without your hp gear, put it on, then mend. Can your rogue do that?<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; I have a Beastlord - who wants a lvl 20 monk when you could have a lvl<br />
&gt; 20 Beastlord??  You get a pet that can proc for damage thrown in with<br />
&gt; a Beastlord at that level...<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
Why compare a pet class with a pure melee? It seems you are happier with<br />
your rogue and beastlord, but are annoyed by the monk because FD &amp; mend<br />
aren't working, and you aren't putting out the same amount of damage, but<br />
are only weilding PSUs. Max out FD &amp; mend, get a couple of fighting batons<br />
(25pp each) and out a couple more levels under your belt. . Pair up with a<br />
druid or a shaman - both awsome combos. Pair up with a necro/sk/ranger and<br />
do some fear kiting.<br />
<br />
Take the lead and start your own groups - lo and behold, there's a monk in a<br />
group. Get people used to having a monk around. Every time I use the LFG<br />
tool, there's maybe 2-3 groups looking for players, but at least 50 players<br />
looking for groups. I can only attribute it to laziness than any one of<br />
those players doesn't start a group and invite those other players. Take a<br />
look next time - how many groups can you make out of all those players LFG?<br />
And don't fall for the trap of believing &quot;you need a full group for the xp<br />
bonus&quot; - you may get 20% extra for a full group, but it's still split 6<br />
ways - 20% each. If you only have 2 in your group, it's 51% each. Once a<br />
group has enough players to bring a constant stream of mobs down with<br />
little/no downtime, that's how big the group needs to be.<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt; I have to say that I rarely, if ever, come across a monk these days,<br />
&gt; at least on my server.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;</font><br />
<br />
I might go and start a monk on your server, for when Innoruuk is down for<br />
&quot;emergency maintenance&quot; again ;-)<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt;<br />
&gt; Palindrome</font><br />
<br />
<br />
